@startuml

actor USER

box "ESP32 BOX"
participant ESP32
participant "MQTT Publisher" as MQTTPUB
participant "ESP32 WEB" as ESPWEB
end box

participant "MQTT Broker" as MQTTBROKER
participant Server
participant "PostgreSQL" as DB
participant WEB

activate USER

USER ->> ESP32 ++: Power ON

ESP32 -> ESP32 ++: 0. Init NVS, LEDs, WiFi (APSTA mode)\n\
1. Read saved WiFi credentials from NVS\n\
2. If found: try STA connect with saved creds

alt Saved credentials connect successfully
  ESP32 -->> ESP32 --: led(1, green_steady)\nSkip provisioning
else No saved creds or connection failed
  ESP32 -> ESP32 ++: Activate hotspot\n\
  SSID = device_id (GB-{MAC})\n\
  Password = first 8 hex chars of MAC\n\
  Start temp_monitor (hibernate cycle)\n\
  Start HTTP server on :80\n\
  led(1, blue_blinking)
  note over ESP32: AP credentials derived from MAC address
  USER ->> ESP32: Connect to device AP (for configuration)
  USER -> ESPWEB ++: GET on http://192.168.4.1:80
  ESPWEB -->> USER: OK 200 /index.html

  ref over USER, ESPWEB : **Phase 1: WiFi + MQTT Broker Configuration**\nSee **phase1-wifi-setup.puml**
  ESP32 -->> ESP32 --
end

note over ESP32: GreenBox is now connected\nto the global internet.

deactivate USER

ref over ESP32, DB : **Phase 2: Device Registration via MQTT**\nSee **phase2-mqtt-registration.puml**

ref over USER, WEB : **Phase 3: Configuration Protocol**\nSee **phase3-config-protocol.puml**

ref over ESP32, DB : **Phase 4: Watering Event Reporting**\nSee **phase4-watering-events.puml**

ref over USER, WEB : **Phase 5: User Data Viewing**\nSee **phase5-user-data-viewing.puml**

@enduml
